Your `dir=&quot;rtl&quot;` direction is only for display. If you open your devtools and look at the content, it&#39;s still ltr format, so when you copy it, it&#39;s still `hello`.

You could do a bit of javascript magic to reverse the string, and then place it back into your element:

```lang javascript
const bdo = document.getElementsByTagName(&#39;bdo&#39;)[0];
const str = bdo.textContent;

bdo.textContent = reverseStr(str);

function reverseStr(str) {
  strArr = str.split(&#39;&#39;);
  
  strArr.reverse();
  
  reversedStr = strArr.join(&#39;&#39;);
  
  return reversedStr;
 
}
```

Working [fiddle](https://jsfiddle.net/brettgaynor/dtfhzgbk/10/)

If you do this, you don&#39;t need the `dir` attribute at all.

