I can assume that your devices have different screen sizes and density. Therefore different resources are used. 

In order to get drawable for a specific screen size you can use the code below:

    Drawable drawable = resources.getDrawableForDensity(id, DisplayMetrics.DENSITY_XHIGH, theme);

Furthermore, you can try to reduce the size of the image:

    BitmapFactory.Options options = new BitmapFactory.Options();
    options.inJustDecodeBounds = true;
    options.inSampleSize = 3; 
    BitmapFactory.decodeResource(getResources(), R.mipmap.hqimage, options);

But generally, you cannot always be sure that the image will consume the same amount of memory, it depends on various factors.

Hope this helps.

